column7: This sample is localized in English and German using LocBaml as well as a few Resx resources.

The following demonstrates a rather annoying bug in WPF where a change of culture apparently is not reflected in bindings. In the following text blocks the display is always in the OS culture, and not the current culture which is displayed as the first item. Testing a some "quoted text as well". The workaround for this problem is to explicitly set the x:Language attribute in the document (not done here).
